The paper deals with the dynamics of finite dynamical systems on graphs, which is a topic that falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the convergence of these systems, which is a topic in both Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the complexity of the dynamics, which is a topic in both Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the boolean case, which is a topic in both Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Theory of Computation (cs.IT).
